window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>An absurd tale that blends the ridiculous and the heartfelt.</p> <p>A runaway bride, a reclusive man, and a tiger who dreams of the forest. They all want one thing: freedom. To escape her father’s tyranny, Avni agrees to a marriage she doesn’t want. On the wedding day, a tiger crashes the ceremony, and Amit, a teacher she once met, tries to save the day. He rescues her, and they elope.<br> But here’s the catch: the tiger, Mastaan Singh, follows them.<br> The story could’ve ended there. Our lovers had their freedom, right?<br> But what begins as a bid for freedom quickly turns strange as Amit grows increasingly obsessed with the tiger.<br> Is Mastaan merely a beast, or a second chance at life—both Amit and Avni?</p>"; 
